textDelta: Rising incomes and urbanization are causing a rise in what food commodities? There is no definitive answer to this question as it depends on a number of factors, such as the level of income and population density of a city. However, some food commodities that may be rising in price as a result of this trend include meat, milk, and eggs.
Why does an electrical current travel faster through muscle than through fat? The electrical current travels faster through muscle than through fat because muscle is more conductive than fat.

Does muscle contain more water than fat? The answer to this question is not definitive. Muscle and fat are both types of tissue, and while muscle contains more water than fat, it is not clear whether this is because muscle is more porous or because muscle contains more water per unit mass.

Why do countries try to protect their own firms from exposure to the world market when international trade always benefits both countries? There are a few reasons why countries might try to protect their own firms from exposure to the world market. One reason is that a country may believe that its own industry is more innovative or valuable than other industries and that its firms are better able to compete in the global market. Another reason may be that a country may believe that its own industry is more important to its economy or that its industry is more important to its national security.

The cost of free trade is often concentrated in the hands of a few countries, and this can prevent companies from benefiting both countries. Another reason is that the international conflicts that can arise can prevent trade from benefiting both countries.
